INSERT INTO public.rep_sources (rep_id, source_type, url, title, content, content_hash) VALUES
  (20, 'official_page', 'https://clyde.house.gov/issues/issue/?IssueID=14892', 'Protecting Life', 'issues
Protecting Life
Share on Facebook
Share on Twitter
Print this Page
Share by Email
At a time when so many leaders are pushing anti-life policies, it is more important than ever that we take a stand for our nation’s innocent unborn. As I build out my pro-life agenda, I have developed two leading principles on which I will never waver when it comes to protecting life.
First and foremost, I believe that not one taxpayer dollar should be allowed to fund abortion programs and services. The Hyde Amendment – a provision that blocks federal funds from being used for abortions – and other similar provisions are under attack as Democrats push their radical agenda. I am committed to opposing all legislation that weakens these long-standing bipartisan provisions.
Secondly, I believe that life begins at the moment of conception, and thus, abortions should be abolished entirely, except in the rare instances when the life of the mother is at risk. I recognize that our progress towards this goal will be slow and difficult, but I am committed to doing everything in my capacity as a member of Congress to protect the sanctity of life. Remember, our Declaration of Independence boldly proclaims, "We hold these truths to be self-evident... life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness. The first unalienable right stated was life.
